1. RC: Replication + Controllers:

1. reliability (Self-healing): if pod get crash then it automatically 
   delete the pod create new one .
2. Scalability(horizontal): on demand we can add pod number for existing
   if traffic is increased.

--replicas=1
--replicas=2:

      pod1     pod2

Controllers: it ensure the desired are running .

Ref. URL : https://kubernetes.io/docs/concepts/workloads/controllers/replicationcontroller/
kubectl create -f rc.yaml  or kubectl apply -f rc.yml   
kubectl get rc
kubectl scale --replicas=4 rc krnetwork   or  kubectl edit rc krnetwork
kubectl scale --replicas=0 rc krnetwork 

kubectl apply -f rc.yml   # This is used if you changed in manifest & want to apply changes.. It works both create & apply

kubectl edit rc zaved -n web
